{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UmBjBADJk9SDj9ynpuZZXb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Orbit camera with spherical coordinates, view/projection matrices.\"\"\"\n     2→\n     3→import math\n     4→import numpy as np\n     5→\n     6→\n     7→class OrbitCamera:\n     8→    \"\"\"Orbit camera around a target point using spherical coordinates.\n     9→\n    10→    Controls: right-drag=orbit, scroll=zoom, middle-drag=pan.\n    11→    \"\"\"\n    12→\n    13→    def __init__(\n    14→        self,\n    15→        target: np.ndarray = None,\n    16→        distance: float = 3.0,\n    17→        azimuth: float = 0.0,\n    18→        elevation: float = 30.0,\n    19→        fov: float = 45.0,\n    20→        near: float = 0.01,\n    21→        far: float = 100.0,\n    22→    ):\n    23→        self.target = np.array(target if target is not None else [0.0, 0.0, 0.0], dtype=np.float32)\n    24→        self.distance = distance\n    25→        self.azimuth = azimuth      # degrees, horizontal rotation\n    26→        self.elevation = elevation  # degrees, vertical rotation\n    27→        self.fov = fov              # vertical field of view in degrees\n    28→        self.near = near\n    29→        self.far = far\n    30→        self.aspect = 16.0 / 9.0\n    31→\n    32→        # Zoom limits\n    33→        self.min_distance = 0.1\n    34→        self.max_distance = 50.0\n    35→\n    36→        # Elevation limits (avoid gimbal lock)\n    37→        self.min_elevation = -89.0\n    38→        self.max_elevation = 89.0\n    39→\n    40→        # Sensitivity\n    41→        self.orbit_sensitivity = 0.3\n    42→        self.zoom_sensitivity = 0.15\n    43→        self.pan_sensitivity = 0.003\n    44→\n    45→    @property\n    46→    def position(self) -> np.ndarray:\n    47→        \"\"\"Camera position in world space computed from spherical coords.\"\"\"\n    48→        az = math.radians(self.azimuth)\n    49→        el = math.radians(self.elevation)\n    50→        cos_el = math.cos(el)\n    51→        x = self.target[0] + self.distance * cos_el * math.sin(az)\n    52→        y = self.target[1] + self.distance * math.sin(el)\n    53→        z = self.target[2] + self.distance * cos_el * math.cos(az)\n    54→        return np.array([x, y, z], dtype=np.float32)\n    55→\n    56→    def orbit(self, dx: float, dy: float):\n    57→        \"\"\"Rotate camera around target. dx/dy in pixels.\"\"\"\n    58→        self.azimuth -= dx * self.orbit_sensitivity\n    59→        self.elevation += dy * self.orbit_sensitivity\n    60→        self.elevation = max(self.min_elevation, min(self.max_elevation, self.elevation))\n    61→\n    62→    def zoom(self, delta: float):\n    63→        \"\"\"Zoom in/out. Positive delta = zoom in.\"\"\"\n    64→        factor = 1.0 - delta * self.zoom_sensitivity\n    65→        self.distance *= factor\n    66→        self.distance = max(self.min_distance, min(self.max_distance, self.distance))\n    67→\n    68→    def pan(self, dx: float, dy: float):\n    69→        \"\"\"Pan the camera (move target). dx/dy in pixels.\"\"\"\n    70→        az = math.radians(self.azimuth)\n    71→        # Right vector (horizontal)\n    72→        right = np.array([math.cos(az), 0.0, -math.sin(az)], dtype=np.float32)\n    73→        # Up vector (world up projected)\n    74→        up = np.array([0.0, 1.0, 0.0], dtype=np.float32)\n    75→\n    76→        scale = self.distance * self.pan_sensitivity\n    77→        self.target -= right * dx * scale\n    78→        self.target += up * dy * scale\n    79→\n    80→    def view_matrix(self) -> np.ndarray:\n    81→        \"\"\"Compute 4x4 view matrix (look-at).\"\"\"\n    82→        eye = self.position\n    83→        center = self.target\n    84→        up = np.array([0.0, 1.0, 0.0], dtype=np.float32)\n    85→        return _look_at(eye, center, up)\n    86→\n    87→    def projection_matrix(self) -> np.ndarray:\n    88→        \"\"\"Compute 4x4 perspective projection matrix.\"\"\"\n    89→        return _perspective(self.fov, self.aspect, self.near, self.far)\n    90→\n    91→    def set_aspect(self, width: int, height: int):\n    92→        if height > 0:\n    93→            self.aspect = width / height\n    94→\n    95→\n    96→def _look_at(eye: np.ndarray, center: np.ndarray, up: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    97→    \"\"\"Compute OpenGL-style look-at view matrix.\"\"\"\n    98→    f = center - eye\n    99→    f = f / np.linalg.norm(f)\n   100→    s = np.cross(f, up)\n   101→    s = s / np.linalg.norm(s)\n   102→    u = np.cross(s, f)\n   103→\n   104→    m = np.eye(4, dtype=np.float32)\n   105→    m[0, 0] = s[0]; m[0, 1] = s[1]; m[0, 2] = s[2]\n   106→    m[1, 0] = u[0]; m[1, 1] = u[1]; m[1, 2] = u[2]\n   107→    m[2, 0] = -f[0]; m[2, 1] = -f[1]; m[2, 2] = -f[2]\n   108→    m[0, 3] = -np.dot(s, eye)\n   109→    m[1, 3] = -np.dot(u, eye)\n   110→    m[2, 3] = np.dot(f, eye)\n   111→    return m\n   112→\n   113→\n   114→def _perspective(fov_deg: float, aspect: float, near: float, far: float) -> np.ndarray:\n   115→    \"\"\"Compute OpenGL-style perspective projection matrix.\"\"\"\n   116→    f = 1.0 / math.tan(math.radians(fov_deg) / 2.0)\n   117→    m = np.zeros((4, 4), dtype=np.float32)\n   118→    m[0, 0] = f / aspect\n   119→    m[1, 1] = f\n   120→    m[2, 2] = (far + near) / (near - far)\n   121→    m[2, 3] = (2.0 * far * near) / (near - far)\n   122→    m[3, 2] = -1.0\n   123→    return m\n   124→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HNB9ThQmhAKuNXhSk34vjN","session_id":"20e7fc32-9409-45e1-9ca1-0f98b4ecc786","uuid":"0e030d5e-3412-4cef-b193-e27c2c91592e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011vmaV3PebiDg2jWLnrgeRo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Material property table and interaction matrix for multi-material SPH.\n     2→\n     3→Defines 16 materials (IDs 0-15) as Python dataclasses, a 32x32 interaction\n     4→matrix, and an upload_to_gpu() function that copies both tables to CUDA\n     5→constant memory via CuPy RawModule symbol lookup.\n     6→\n     7→Struct layout matches fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/common.cuh exactly.\n     8→\n     9→Constant-memory symbols\n    10→-----------------------\n    11→- ``c_materials``   : MaterialProps[32]\n    12→- ``c_interactions`` : Interaction[32][32]\n    13→\"\"\"\n    14→\n    15→from __future__ import annotations\n    16→\n    17→import dataclasses\n    18→import os\n    19→from typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\n    20→\n    21→import numpy as np\n    22→\n    23→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    24→# Numpy structured dtypes matching the C structs in common.cuh\n    25→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    26→\n    27→MATERIAL_PROPS_DTYPE = np.dtype(\n    28→    [\n    29→        (\"rest_density\", np.float32),\n    30→        (\"eos_stiffness\", np.float32),\n    31→        (\"eos_gamma\", np.float32),\n    32→        (\"base_viscosity\", np.float32),\n    33→        (\"friction_coeff\", np.float32),\n    34→        (\"cohesion\", np.float32),\n    35→        (\"buoyancy_extra\", np.float32),\n    36→        (\"thermal_conductivity\", np.float32),\n    37→        (\"heat_capacity\", np.float32),\n    38→        (\"temp_melt\", np.float32),\n    39→        (\"temp_boil\", np.float32),\n    40→        (\"temp_ignite\", np.float32),\n    41→        (\"behavior_class\", np.int32),\n    42→        (\"color_r\", np.float32),\n    43→        (\"color_g\", np.float32),\n    44→        (\"color_b\", np.float32),\n    45→    ],\n    46→    align=True,\n    47→)\n    48→\n    49→INTERACTION_DTYPE = np.dtype(\n    50→    [\n    51→        (\"reaction_rate\", np.float32),\n    52→        (\"heat_exchange\", np.float32),\n    53→    ],\n    54→    align=True,\n    55→)\n    56→\n    57→# Compile-time size checks (must match sizeof(MaterialProps) and sizeof(Interaction))\n    58→assert MATERIAL_PROPS_DTYPE.itemsize == 64, (\n    59→    f\"MaterialProps size mismatch: {MATERIAL_PROPS_DTYPE.itemsize} != 64\"\n    60→)\n    61→assert INTERACTION_DTYPE.itemsize == 8, (\n    62→    f\"Interaction size mismatch: {INTERACTION_DTYPE.itemsize} != 8\"\n    63→)\n    64→\n    65→MAX_MATERIALS = 32  # slots in constant memory (IDs 0-31)\n    66→NUM_DEFINED = 16  # IDs 0-15 are defined; 16-31 reserved (zeroed)\n    67→\n    68→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    69→# BehaviorClass enum (mirrors common.cuh)\n    70→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    71→\n    72→FLUID = 0\n    73→GRANULAR = 1\n    74→GAS = 2\n    75→STATIC = 3\n    76→\n    77→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    78→# MaterialDef dataclass\n    79→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    80→\n    81→\n    82→@dataclasses.dataclass\n    83→class MaterialDef:\n    84→    \"\"\"Python-side definition of a single material.\n    85→\n    86→    Field names and semantics match the ``MaterialProps`` C struct in common.cuh.\n    87→    \"\"\"\n    88→\n    89→    id: int\n    90→    name: str  # human-readable label (not uploaded to GPU)\n    91→    rest_density: float  # kg/m^3\n    92→    eos_stiffness: float  # Tait EOS k\n    93→    eos_gamma: float  # Tait EOS exponent (7 for liquid, 1 for gas)\n    94→    base_viscosity: float  # Pa*s\n    95→    friction_coeff: float  # mu_s for granular friction\n    96→    cohesion: float  # cohesion coefficient\n    97→    buoyancy_extra: float  # extra buoyancy factor for gas\n    98→    thermal_conductivity: float  # W/(m*K)\n    99→    heat_capacity: float  # J/(kg*K)\n   100→    temp_melt: float  # Kelvin\n   101→    temp_boil: float  # Kelvin\n   102→    temp_ignite: float  # Kelvin (0 = non-flammable)\n   103→    behavior_class: int  # BehaviorClass enum value\n   104→    color_r: float  # default material color R [0,1]\n   105→    color_g: float  # default material color G [0,1]\n   106→    color_b: float  # default material color B [0,1]\n   107→\n   108→    def to_numpy(self) -> np.void:\n   109→        \"\"\"Pack into a single numpy structured-array element.\"\"\"\n   110→        return np.array(\n   111→            (\n   112→                self.rest_density,\n   113→                self.eos_stiffness,\n   114→                self.eos_gamma,\n   115→                self.base_viscosity,\n   116→                self.friction_coeff,\n   117→                self.cohesion,\n   118→                self.buoyancy_extra,\n   119→                self.thermal_conductivity,\n   120→                self.heat_capacity,\n   121→                self.temp_melt,\n   122→                self.temp_boil,\n   123→                self.temp_ignite,\n   124→                self.behavior_class,\n   125→                self.color_r,\n   126→                self.color_g,\n   127→                self.color_b,\n   128→            ),\n   129→            dtype=MATERIAL_PROPS_DTYPE,\n   130→        )\n   131→\n   132→\n   133→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   134→# Material ID constants\n   135→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   136→\n   137→DEAD = 0\n   138→STONE = 1\n   139→SAND = 2\n   140→DIRT = 3\n   141→GRAVEL = 4\n   142→WATER = 5\n   143→OIL = 6\n   144→LAVA = 7\n   145→ACID = 8\n   146→WOOD = 9\n   147→METAL = 10\n   148→ICE = 11\n   149→STEAM = 12\n   150→SMOKE = 13\n   151→FIRE = 14\n   152→GUNPOWDER = 15\n   153→\n   154→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   155→# Material definitions (16 entries, IDs 0-15)\n   156→#\n   157→# Property values chosen for a falling-sand / multi-material SPH game:\n   158→#   - rest_density in kg/m^3 (approximate real-world)\n   159→#   - eos_stiffness: Tait EOS pressure coefficient (game-tuned)\n   160→#   - eos_gamma: 7 for FLUID/GRANULAR, 1 for GAS, 0 for STATIC/DEAD\n   161→#   - base_viscosity in Pa*s (scaled for game feel)\n   162→#   - temperatures in Kelvin\n   163→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   164→\n   165→MATERIALS: Dict[int, MaterialDef] = {\n   166→    DEAD: MaterialDef(\n   167→        id=DEAD, name=\"DEAD\",\n   168→        rest_density=0.0, eos_stiffness=0.0, eos_gamma=0.0,\n   169→        base_viscosity=0.0, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   170→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.0, heat_capacity=0.0,\n   171→        temp_melt=0.0, temp_boil=0.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   172→        behavior_class=STATIC,\n   173→        color_r=0.0, color_g=0.0, color_b=0.0,\n   174→    ),\n   175→    STONE: MaterialDef(\n   176→        id=STONE, name=\"STONE\",\n   177→        rest_density=2600.0, eos_stiffness=50.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   178→        base_viscosity=0.0, friction_coeff=0.7, cohesion=0.5,\n   179→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=2.0, heat_capacity=800.0,\n   180→        temp_melt=1500.0, temp_boil=3000.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   181→        behavior_class=STATIC,\n   182→        color_r=0.5, color_g=0.5, color_b=0.5,\n   183→    ),\n   184→    SAND: MaterialDef(\n   185→        id=SAND, name=\"SAND\",\n   186→        rest_density=1600.0, eos_stiffness=20.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   187→        base_viscosity=0.5, friction_coeff=0.6, cohesion=0.0,\n   188→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.3, heat_capacity=830.0,\n   189→        temp_melt=1700.0, temp_boil=2500.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   190→        behavior_class=GRANULAR,\n   191→        color_r=0.76, color_g=0.70, color_b=0.50,\n   192→    ),\n   193→    DIRT: MaterialDef(\n   194→        id=DIRT, name=\"DIRT\",\n   195→        rest_density=1500.0, eos_stiffness=18.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   196→        base_viscosity=0.8, friction_coeff=0.5, cohesion=0.1,\n   197→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.25, heat_capacity=900.0,\n   198→        temp_melt=1400.0, temp_boil=2200.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   199→        behavior_class=GRANULAR,\n   200→        color_r=0.55, color_g=0.35, color_b=0.17,\n   201→    ),\n   202→    GRAVEL: MaterialDef(\n   203→        id=GRAVEL, name=\"GRAVEL\",\n   204→        rest_density=1800.0, eos_stiffness=25.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   205→        base_viscosity=0.3, friction_coeff=0.65, cohesion=0.0,\n   206→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.5, heat_capacity=840.0,\n   207→        temp_melt=1500.0, temp_boil=2800.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   208→        behavior_class=GRANULAR,\n   209→        color_r=0.45, color_g=0.42, color_b=0.40,\n   210→    ),\n   211→    WATER: MaterialDef(\n   212→        id=WATER, name=\"WATER\",\n   213→        rest_density=1000.0, eos_stiffness=10.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   214→        base_viscosity=1.0, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   215→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.6, heat_capacity=4186.0,\n   216→        temp_melt=273.0, temp_boil=373.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   217→        behavior_class=FLUID,\n   218→        color_r=0.2, color_g=0.5, color_b=0.9,\n   219→    ),\n   220→    OIL: MaterialDef(\n   221→        id=OIL, name=\"OIL\",\n   222→        rest_density=800.0, eos_stiffness=8.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   223→        base_viscosity=5.0, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   224→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.15, heat_capacity=2000.0,\n   225→        temp_melt=250.0, temp_boil=570.0, temp_ignite=480.0,\n   226→        behavior_class=FLUID,\n   227→        color_r=0.15, color_g=0.10, color_b=0.05,\n   228→    ),\n   229→    LAVA: MaterialDef(\n   230→        id=LAVA, name=\"LAVA\",\n   231→        rest_density=2500.0, eos_stiffness=30.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   232→        base_viscosity=100.0, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   233→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=1.5, heat_capacity=1000.0,\n   234→        temp_melt=1000.0, temp_boil=2500.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   235→        behavior_class=FLUID,\n   236→        color_r=1.0, color_g=0.3, color_b=0.0,\n   237→    ),\n   238→    ACID: MaterialDef(\n   239→        id=ACID, name=\"ACID\",\n   240→        rest_density=1200.0, eos_stiffness=10.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   241→        base_viscosity=1.5, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   242→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.5, heat_capacity=2500.0,\n   243→        temp_melt=250.0, temp_boil=380.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   244→        behavior_class=FLUID,\n   245→        color_r=0.4, color_g=1.0, color_b=0.1,\n   246→    ),\n   247→    WOOD: MaterialDef(\n   248→        id=WOOD, name=\"WOOD\",\n   249→        rest_density=600.0, eos_stiffness=15.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   250→        base_viscosity=0.0, friction_coeff=0.5, cohesion=0.3,\n   251→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.15, heat_capacity=1700.0,\n   252→        temp_melt=0.0, temp_boil=0.0, temp_ignite=570.0,\n   253→        behavior_class=STATIC,\n   254→        color_r=0.55, color_g=0.35, color_b=0.12,\n   255→    ),\n   256→    METAL: MaterialDef(\n   257→        id=METAL, name=\"METAL\",\n   258→        rest_density=7800.0, eos_stiffness=100.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   259→        base_viscosity=0.0, friction_coeff=0.6, cohesion=1.0,\n   260→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=50.0, heat_capacity=450.0,\n   261→        temp_melt=1800.0, temp_boil=3300.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   262→        behavior_class=STATIC,\n   263→        color_r=0.7, color_g=0.7, color_b=0.75,\n   264→    ),\n   265→    ICE: MaterialDef(\n   266→        id=ICE, name=\"ICE\",\n   267→        rest_density=917.0, eos_stiffness=15.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   268→        base_viscosity=0.0, friction_coeff=0.1, cohesion=0.2,\n   269→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=2.2, heat_capacity=2090.0,\n   270→        temp_melt=273.0, temp_boil=373.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   271→        behavior_class=STATIC,\n   272→        color_r=0.7, color_g=0.9, color_b=1.0,\n   273→    ),\n   274→    STEAM: MaterialDef(\n   275→        id=STEAM, name=\"STEAM\",\n   276→        rest_density=0.6, eos_stiffness=3.0, eos_gamma=1.0,\n   277→        base_viscosity=0.01, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   278→        buoyancy_extra=0.01, thermal_conductivity=0.025, heat_capacity=2010.0,\n   279→        temp_melt=0.0, temp_boil=0.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   280→        behavior_class=GAS,\n   281→        color_r=0.85, color_g=0.85, color_b=0.90,\n   282→    ),\n   283→    SMOKE: MaterialDef(\n   284→        id=SMOKE, name=\"SMOKE\",\n   285→        rest_density=0.3, eos_stiffness=2.5, eos_gamma=1.0,\n   286→        base_viscosity=0.01, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   287→        buoyancy_extra=0.005, thermal_conductivity=0.02, heat_capacity=1000.0,\n   288→        temp_melt=0.0, temp_boil=0.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   289→        behavior_class=GAS,\n   290→        color_r=0.3, color_g=0.3, color_b=0.3,\n   291→    ),\n   292→    FIRE: MaterialDef(\n   293→        id=FIRE, name=\"FIRE\",\n   294→        rest_density=0.2, eos_stiffness=4.0, eos_gamma=1.0,\n   295→        base_viscosity=0.01, friction_coeff=0.0, cohesion=0.0,\n   296→        buoyancy_extra=0.02, thermal_conductivity=0.05, heat_capacity=1000.0,\n   297→        temp_melt=0.0, temp_boil=0.0, temp_ignite=0.0,\n   298→        behavior_class=GAS,\n   299→        color_r=1.0, color_g=0.6, color_b=0.1,\n   300→    ),\n   301→    GUNPOWDER: MaterialDef(\n   302→        id=GUNPOWDER, name=\"GUNPOWDER\",\n   303→        rest_density=1700.0, eos_stiffness=20.0, eos_gamma=7.0,\n   304→        base_viscosity=0.0, friction_coeff=0.5, cohesion=0.0,\n   305→        buoyancy_extra=0.0, thermal_conductivity=0.2, heat_capacity=800.0,\n   306→        temp_melt=0.0, temp_boil=0.0, temp_ignite=480.0,\n   307→        behavior_class=GRANULAR,\n   308→        color_r=0.2, color_g=0.2, color_b=0.2,\n   309→    ),\n   310→}\n   311→\n   312→assert len(MATERIALS) == NUM_DEFINED\n   313→\n   314→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   315→# 32x32 Interaction matrix\n   316→#\n   317→# Each (i, j) pair stores reaction_rate and heat_exchange.\n   318→# Only non-trivial pairs are listed; everything else defaults to zero.\n   319→# Symmetric: both (a,b) and (b,a) are set.\n   320→#\n   321→# Key interactions:\n   322→#   water + lava   -> steam (high heat exchange)\n   323→#   acid  + metal  -> reaction_rate 0.3\n   324→#   acid  + stone  -> slow corrosion\n   325→#   acid  + wood   -> slow corrosion\n   326→#   fire  + wood   -> burning\n   327→#   fire  + oil    -> fast burning\n   328→#   fire  + gunpowder -> explosion\n   329→#   lava  + ice    -> steam + stone\n   330→#   lava  + wood   -> burning\n   331→#   water + ice    -> melting\n   332→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   333→\n   334→# (mat_a, mat_b): (reaction_rate, heat_exchange)\n   335→_INTERACTION_PAIRS: List[Tuple[int, int, float, float]] = [\n   336→    # water interactions\n   337→    (WATER, LAVA, 0.5, 5.0),         # water + lava -> steam, cools lava\n   338→    (WATER, ICE, 0.1, 2.0),          # water near ice -> freezing/melting\n   339→    (WATER, FIRE, 0.8, 3.0),         # water extinguishes fire\n   340→    (WATER, ACID, 0.05, 0.5),        # water dilutes acid slowly\n   341→    # lava interactions\n   342→    (LAVA, ICE, 0.6, 6.0),           # lava melts ice rapidly\n   343→    (LAVA, WOOD, 0.7, 4.0),          # lava ignites wood\n   344→    (LAVA, METAL, 0.05, 3.0),        # lava heats metal\n   345→    (LAVA, STONE, 0.0, 2.0),         # lava heats stone (no reaction, just heat)\n   346→    (LAVA, OIL, 0.8, 5.0),           # lava ignites oil\n   347→    (LAVA, GUNPOWDER, 0.9, 5.0),     # lava detonates gunpowder\n   348→    # acid interactions\n   349→    (ACID, STONE, 0.15, 0.3),        # acid slowly corrodes stone\n   350→    (ACID, METAL, 0.3, 0.5),         # acid corrodes metal\n   351→    (ACID, WOOD, 0.2, 0.2),          # acid corrodes wood\n   352→    (ACID, DIRT, 0.1, 0.1),          # acid dissolves dirt\n   353→    (ACID, ICE, 0.2, 1.0),           # acid melts ice\n   354→    # fire interactions\n   355→    (FIRE, WOOD, 0.6, 2.0),          # fire burns wood\n   356→    (FIRE, OIL, 0.8, 3.0),           # fire burns oil quickly\n   357→    (FIRE, GUNPOWDER, 0.9, 4.0),     # fire detonates gunpowder\n   358→    (FIRE, ICE, 0.3, 2.5),           # fire melts ice\n   359→    (FIRE, SMOKE, 0.0, 0.5),         # fire produces smoke (heat only)\n   360→    # oil interactions\n   361→    (OIL, WATER, 0.0, 0.3),          # oil floats on water (no reaction, low heat)\n   362→    # ice + steam\n   363→    (ICE, STEAM, 0.2, 1.5),          # steam melts ice\n   364→    # metal + fire\n   365→    (FIRE, METAL, 0.0, 2.0),         # fire heats metal (no reaction, heat only)\n   366→    # stone + fire\n   367→    (FIRE, STONE, 0.0, 0.5),         # fire heats stone slowly\n   368→]\n   369→\n   370→\n   371→def build_interaction_matrix() -> np.ndarray:\n   372→    \"\"\"Build the 32x32 interaction matrix as a numpy structured array.\n   373→\n   374→    Returns a (32, 32) array of Interaction structs. Interactions are\n   375→    symmetric: setting (a, b) also sets (b, a).\n   376→    \"\"\"\n   377→    matrix = np.zeros((MAX_MATERIALS, MAX_MATERIALS), dtype=INTERACTION_DTYPE)\n   378→    for a, b, rate, heat in _INTERACTION_PAIRS:\n   379→        matrix[a][b][\"reaction_rate\"] = rate\n   380→        matrix[a][b][\"heat_exchange\"] = heat\n   381→        matrix[b][a][\"reaction_rate\"] = rate\n   382→        matrix[b][a][\"heat_exchange\"] = heat\n   383→    return matrix\n   384→\n   385→\n   386→def build_material_array() -> np.ndarray:\n   387→    \"\"\"Build the MaterialProps[32] array as a numpy structured array.\n   388→\n   389→    IDs 0-15 come from MATERIALS; IDs 16-31 are zeroed (reserved).\n   390→    \"\"\"\n   391→    arr = np.zeros(MAX_MATERIALS, dtype=MATERIAL_PROPS_DTYPE)\n   392→    for mat_id, mat_def in MATERIALS.items():\n   393→        arr[mat_id] = mat_def.to_numpy()\n   394→    return arr\n   395→\n   396→\n   397→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   398→# GPU upload via CuPy RawModule\n   399→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   400→\n   401→# Cached CuPy RawModule (compiled on first use)\n   402→_module: Optional[object] = None\n   403→\n   404→\n   405→def _ensure_ptx_if_needed() -> None:\n   406→    \"\"\"Force PTX compilation when the GPU arch exceeds NVRTC's max sm target.\"\"\"\n   407→    from cupy.cuda import compiler as _compiler\n   408→    from cupy.cuda import device as _device\n   409→\n   410→    gpu_cc = _device.Device().compute_capability\n   411→    nvrtc_max = _compiler._get_max_compute_capability()\n   412→    if int(gpu_cc) > int(nvrtc_max):\n   413→        _compiler._use_ptx = True\n   414→        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc, \"_cache\"):\n   415→            _compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc._cache = {}\n   416→        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch, \"_cache\"):\n   417→            _compiler._get_arch._cache = {}\n   418→\n   419→\n   420→def _get_module() -> \"object\":\n   421→    \"\"\"Compile (or return cached) CuPy RawModule with common.cuh included.\"\"\"\n   422→    global _module\n   423→    if _module is None:\n   424→        import cupy\n   425→\n   426→        _ensure_ptx_if_needed()\n   427→        kernel_dir = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"physics\", \"kernels\")\n   428→        # Minimal CUDA source that includes common.cuh for its constant memory\n   429→        # declarations, plus a test kernel for verification.\n   430→        source = r\"\"\"\n   431→#include \"common.cuh\"\n   432→\n   433→extern \"C\" __global__\n   434→void test_read_materials(float* out) {\n   435→    // out[0] = c_materials[5].rest_density   (water -> 1000.0)\n   436→    // out[1] = c_interactions[8][10].reaction_rate  (acid-metal -> 0.3)\n   437→    out[0] = c_materials[5].rest_density;\n   438→    out[1] = c_interactions[8][10].reaction_rate;\n   439→}\n   440→\"\"\"\n   441→        _module = cupy.RawModule(\n   442→            code=source,\n   443→            options=(\"--std=c++11\", f\"-I{kernel_dir}\"),\n   444→        )\n   445→    return _module\n   446→\n   447→\n   448→def upload_to_gpu(module: Optional[object] = None) -> None:\n   449→    \"\"\"Copy MaterialProps[32] and Interaction[32][32] to CUDA constant memory.\n   450→\n   451→    Parameters\n   452→    ----------\n   453→    module : CuPy RawModule, optional\n   454→        If provided, upload to this module's constant memory symbols.\n   455→        If None, uses the internal module from _get_module().\n   456→    \"\"\"\n   457→    import cupy\n   458→\n   459→    cudaMemcpyHostToDevice = 1\n   460→\n   461→    if module is None:\n   462→        module = _get_module()\n   463→\n   464→    h_materials = build_material_array()\n   465→    h_interactions = build_interaction_matrix()\n   466→\n   467→    d_materials_ptr = module.get_global(\"c_materials\")\n   468→    d_interactions_ptr = module.get_global(\"c_interactions\")\n   469→\n   470→    cupy.cuda.runtime.memcpy(\n   471→        int(d_materials_ptr),\n   472→        h_materials.ctypes.data,\n   473→        h_materials.nbytes,\n   474→        cudaMemcpyHostToDevice,\n   475→    )\n   476→\n   477→    cupy.cuda.runtime.memcpy(\n   478→        int(d_interactions_ptr),\n   479→        h_interactions.ctypes.data,\n   480→        h_interactions.nbytes,\n   481→        cudaMemcpyHostToDevice,\n   482→    )\n   483→\n   484→\n   485→def get_module() -> \"object\":\n   486→    \"\"\"Return the compiled CuPy RawModule (public accessor for tests).\"\"\"\n   487→    return _get_module()\n   488→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HNB9ThQmhAKuNXhSk34vjN","session_id":"20e7fc32-9409-45e1-9ca1-0f98b4ecc786","uuid":"5818ee80-545c-43dd-80f0-29608f008985"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CjoLmAtnqRru7MNoEuKqTk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * common.cuh -- Single source of truth for all GPU data layouts.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All .cu kernel files include this header. It defines:\n     5→ *   - BehaviorClass enum\n     6→ *   - MaterialProps / Interaction structs + constant memory arrays\n     7→ *   - GridParams struct + constant memory\n     8→ *   - SimParams / PrecalcParams structs + constant memory\n     9→ *   - packed_info bitfield macros\n    10→ *   - Array type conventions (documented in comments)\n    11→ */\n    12→\n    13→#ifndef FALLINGSAND3D_COMMON_CUH\n    14→#define FALLINGSAND3D_COMMON_CUH\n    15→\n    16→typedef unsigned int uint;\n    17→\n    18→/* ======================================================================\n    19→ * Behavior classes\n    20→ * ====================================================================== */\n    21→\n    22→enum BehaviorClass {\n    23→    FLUID   = 0,\n    24→    GRANULAR = 1,\n    25→    GAS     = 2,\n    26→    STATIC  = 3\n    27→};\n    28→\n    29→/* ======================================================================\n    30→ * MaterialProps -- per-material constants uploaded to constant memory.\n    31→ * 16 fields x 4 bytes = 64 bytes (no extra padding needed).\n    32→ * ====================================================================== */\n    33→\n    34→struct MaterialProps {\n    35→    float rest_density;          // kg/m^3\n    36→    float eos_stiffness;         // Tait EOS k\n    37→    float eos_gamma;             // Tait EOS exponent (7 for liquid, 1 for gas)\n    38→    float base_viscosity;        // Pa*s\n    39→    float friction_coeff;        // mu_s for granular friction\n    40→    float cohesion;              // cohesion coefficient\n    41→    float buoyancy_extra;        // extra buoyancy factor for gas\n    42→    float thermal_conductivity;  // W/(m*K)\n    43→    float heat_capacity;         // J/(kg*K)\n    44→    float temp_melt;             // Kelvin\n    45→    float temp_boil;             // Kelvin\n    46→    float temp_ignite;           // Kelvin (0 = non-flammable)\n    47→    int   behavior_class;        // BehaviorClass enum value\n    48→    float color_r;               // default material color R\n    49→    float color_g;               // default material color G\n    50→    float color_b;               // default material color B\n    51→};\n    52→// Static assert: sizeof(MaterialProps) must be 64 bytes\n    53→\n    54→/* ======================================================================\n    55→ * Interaction -- per-pair (i,j) reaction parameters.\n    56→ * 2 fields x 4 bytes = 8 bytes.\n    57→ * ====================================================================== */\n    58→\n    59→struct Interaction {\n    60→    float reaction_rate;   // reaction speed (0 = no reaction)\n    61→    float heat_exchange;   // heat transfer coefficient between pair\n    62→};\n    63→\n    64→/* ======================================================================\n    65→ * Constant memory: materials and interactions\n    66→ * Total: 32*64 + 32*32*8 = 2048 + 8192 = 10240 bytes (well under 64 KB)\n    67→ * ====================================================================== */\n    68→\n    69→__constant__ MaterialProps c_materials[32];\n    70→__constant__ Interaction   c_interactions[32][32];\n    71→\n    72→/* ======================================================================\n    73→ * GridParams -- uniform grid parameters for spatial hashing.\n    74→ *\n    75→ * grid_res uses int3 (not float3 as in the root-level prototype) for\n    76→ * correct integer arithmetic in hash computation.\n    77→ * ====================================================================== */\n    78→\n    79→struct GridParams {\n    80→    float3 grid_min;    // world-space minimum corner\n    81→    float3 grid_max;    // world-space maximum corner\n    82→    int3   grid_res;    // number of cells per axis\n    83→    float3 grid_delta;  // 1 / cell_size = grid_res / grid_size\n    84→    int    num_cells;   // grid_res.x * grid_res.y * grid_res.z\n    85→};\n    86→\n    87→__constant__ GridParams c_grid;\n    88→\n    89→/* ======================================================================\n    90→ * SimParams -- simulation-wide parameters.\n    91→ *\n    92→ * Uploaded once per frame (or when sim config changes).\n    93→ * ====================================================================== */\n    94→\n    95→struct SimParams {\n    96→    float  smoothing_length;     // h\n    97→    float  smoothing_length_sq;  // h^2\n    98→    float  particle_mass;        // uniform mass per particle\n    99→    float  particle_spacing;     // rest spacing between particles\n   100→    float3 gravity;              // (0, -9.8, 0) typically\n   101→    float  dt;                   // simulation timestep\n   102→    float  restitution;          // wall bounce coefficient\n   103→    float  wall_friction;        // wall friction coefficient\n   104→    float3 world_min;            // simulation domain min\n   105→    float3 world_max;            // simulation domain max\n   106→};\n   107→\n   108→__constant__ SimParams c_sim;\n   109→\n   110→/* ======================================================================\n   111→ * PrecalcParams -- kernel coefficients precomputed from smoothing_length.\n   112→ *\n   113→ * These depend on h and are recomputed when h changes. Stored separately\n   114→ * from SimParams to keep the intent clear.\n   115→ *\n   116→ * Sign convention: pressure_precalc is POSITIVE (+45/(pi*h^6)) because\n   117→ * it absorbs the double negative from the SPH momentum equation.\n   118→ * ====================================================================== */\n   119→\n   120→struct PrecalcParams {\n   121→    float poly6_coeff;           // 315 / (64 * pi * h^9)\n   122→    float spiky_grad_coeff;      // -45 / (pi * h^6)  (negative)\n   123→    float viscosity_lap_coeff;   // 45 / (pi * h^6)\n   124→    float pressure_precalc;      // +45 / (pi * h^6)   (positive, see note)\n   125→    float viscosity_precalc;     // mu * 45 / (pi * h^6)\n   126→};\n   127→\n   128→__constant__ PrecalcParams c_precalc;\n   129→\n   130→/* ======================================================================\n   131→ * packed_info bitfield layout (uint32)\n   132→ *\n   133→ *   Bits [7:0]   material_id    (256 materials max, 32 used)\n   134→ *   Bits [9:8]   behavior_class (FLUID=0, GRANULAR=1, GAS=2, STATIC=3)\n   135→ *   Bit  [10]    is_sleeping    (1 = asleep, skip force computation)\n   136→ *   Bit  [11]    spawn_flag     (1 = just spawned, needs initialization)\n   137→ *   Bit  [12]    just_woke      (1 = woke this frame, needs velocity reset)\n   138→ *   Bits [31:13] reserved\n   139→ * ====================================================================== */\n   140→\n   141→#define GET_MATERIAL_ID(p)  ((p) & 0xFF)\n   142→#define GET_BEHAVIOR(p)     (((p) >> 8) & 0x3)\n   143→#define IS_SLEEPING(p)      (((p) >> 10) & 1)\n   144→#define SET_SLEEPING(p)     ((p) | 0x400)\n   145→#define CLEAR_SLEEPING(p)   ((p) & ~0x400)\n   146→#define HAS_SPAWN_FLAG(p)   (((p) >> 11) & 1)\n   147→#define SET_SPAWN_FLAG(p)   ((p) | 0x800)\n   148→#define HAS_JUST_WOKE(p)    (((p) >> 12) & 1)\n   149→#define MAKE_PACKED(mat, beh) (((mat) & 0xFF) | (((beh) & 0x3) << 8))\n   150→\n   151→/* ======================================================================\n   152→ * Array type conventions (documented per acceptance criteria)\n   153→ *\n   154→ * float4 arrays (w component unused, set to 0):\n   155→ *   position, velocity, veleval, sph_force, color\n   156→ *\n   157→ * float arrays:\n   158→ *   density, mass, temperature, health, lifetime,\n   159→ *   shear_rate, exposure_heat, exposure_corrode\n   160→ *\n   161→ * uint32 arrays:\n   162→ *   packed_info\n   163→ *\n   164→ * uint8 arrays:\n   165→ *   sleep_counter\n   166→ * ====================================================================== */\n   167→\n   168→#endif /* FALLINGSAND3D_COMMON_CUH */\n   169→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HNB9ThQmhAKuNXhSk34vjN","session_id":"20e7fc32-9409-45e1-9ca1-0f98b4ecc786","uuid":"f0eecef6-4b98-4a1a-9372-3823f2d0ee41"}
