{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XJKVmZHESFKVE968rpouwK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * integrate.cu -- K_Integrate kernel: symplectic Euler integration,\n     3→ * impulse-style SDF box boundaries, GAS buoyancy/drag, velocity clamping,\n     4→ * color computation, and writeback to UNSORTED arrays via sort_indexes.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * Per-particle computation:\n     7→ *   1. Compute acceleration: accel = sph_force/mass + gravity + gas_buoyancy\n     8→ *   2. Symplectic Euler: vel_new = vel + dt * accel\n     9→ *   3. GAS drag: vel_new *= (1 - c_drag * dt)\n    10→ *   4. Velocity clamp: |vel| <= velocity_limit\n    11→ *   5. Position update: pos_new = pos + dt * (vel_new + xsph) for FLUID,\n    12→ *      pos_new = pos + dt * vel_new for others\n    13→ *   6. Impulse SDF boundary: 6 planes of box, project out, reflect normal vel\n    14→ *      with restitution, apply Coulomb friction to tangential vel\n    15→ *   7. Compute color from material base color, temperature tint, health fade\n    16→ *   8. Write pos, vel, color to UNSORTED arrays via sort_indexes[i]\n    17→ *\n    18→ * Skips STATIC particles (behavior_class == 3): early return, position unchanged.\n    19→ *\n    20→ * Constant memory used:\n    21→ *   c_sim       -- SimParams from common.cuh (gravity, dt, restitution, etc.)\n    22→ *   c_materials -- MaterialProps[32] from common.cuh (for color lookup)\n    23→ */\n    24→\n    25→#include \"common.cuh\"\n    26→\n    27→/* ======================================================================\n    28→ * Constants\n    29→ * ====================================================================== */\n    30→\n    31→#define GAS_BUOYANCY_BETA  0.01f\n    32→#define GAS_AMBIENT_TEMP   293.0f\n    33→#define GAS_BUOYANCY_G     9.81f\n    34→#define GAS_DRAG_COEFF     2.0f\n    35→#define VELOCITY_LIMIT     50.0f\n    36→#define VELOCITY_LIMIT_SQ  (VELOCITY_LIMIT * VELOCITY_LIMIT)\n    37→\n    38→/* ======================================================================\n    39→ * Impulse-style SDF boundary collision for axis-aligned box.\n    40→ *\n    41→ * For each of 6 planes: if pos penetrates wall, project out and\n    42→ * apply impulse-style velocity correction:\n    43→ *   - Normal velocity reflected with restitution coefficient\n    44→ *   - Tangential velocity reduced by Coulomb friction\n    45→ * ====================================================================== */\n    46→\n    47→__device__ inline void sdf_box_boundary(\n    48→    float3& pos,\n    49→    float3& vel,\n    50→    float3 world_min,\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20e7fc32-9409-45e1-9ca1-0f98b4ecc786","uuid":"c5b718ee-ed9f-4aca-a22a-6227f7cab4e8","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/integrate.cu","content":"/*\n * integrate.cu -- K_Integrate kernel: symplectic Euler integration,\n * impulse-style SDF box boundaries, GAS buoyancy/drag, velocity clamping,\n * color computation, and writeback to UNSORTED arrays via sort_indexes.\n *\n * Per-particle computation:\n *   1. Compute acceleration: accel = sph_force/mass + gravity + gas_buoyancy\n *   2. Symplectic Euler: vel_new = vel + dt * accel\n *   3. GAS drag: vel_new *= (1 - c_drag * dt)\n *   4. Velocity clamp: |vel| <= velocity_limit\n *   5. Position update: pos_new = pos + dt * (vel_new + xsph) for FLUID,\n *      pos_new = pos + dt * vel_new for others\n *   6. Impulse SDF boundary: 6 planes of box, project out, reflect normal vel\n *      with restitution, apply Coulomb friction to tangential vel\n *   7. Compute color from material base color, temperature tint, health fade\n *   8. Write pos, vel, color to UNSORTED arrays via sort_indexes[i]\n *\n * Skips STATIC particles (behavior_class == 3): early return, position unchanged.\n *\n * Constant memory used:\n *   c_sim       -- SimParams from common.cuh (gravity, dt, restitution, etc.)\n *   c_materials -- MaterialProps[32] from common.cuh (for color lookup)\n */\n\n#include \"common.cuh\"\n\n/* ======================================================================\n * Constants\n * ====================================================================== */\n\n#define GAS_BUOYANCY_BETA  0.01f\n#define GAS_AMBIENT_TEMP   293.0f\n#define GAS_BUOYANCY_G     9.81f\n#define GAS_DRAG_COEFF     2.0f\n#define VELOCITY_LIMIT     50.0f\n#define VELOCITY_LIMIT_SQ  (VELOCITY_LIMIT * VELOCITY_LIMIT)\n\n/* ======================================================================\n * Impulse-style SDF boundary collision for axis-aligned box.\n *\n * For each of 6 planes: if pos penetrates wall, project out and\n * apply impulse-style velocity correction:\n *   - Normal velocity reflected with restitution coefficient\n *   - Tangential velocity reduced by Coulomb friction\n * ====================================================================== */\n\n__device__ inline void sdf_box_boundary(\n    float3& pos,\n    float3& vel,\n    float3 world_min,","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":318}}}
