{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01StGbwGVBtcKfNpLMAg9UXX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The kernel writes directly to `sph_force_out[index_i]` and `veleval_out[index_i]` - it doesn't accumulate. It assigns the full value. So there's no initialization issue. The STATIC/SLEEPING early returns also write zero force and copy velocity. This is correct.\n\nEverything looks solid. Let me now verify the particle count math for the initial scene to make sure we get approximately 10K each:\n\n- Water cube: (-0.2, 0.3, -0.2) to (0.2, 0.7, 0.2), spacing 0.02\n  - x: (0.4/0.02) = 20 particles\n  - y: (0.4/0.02) = 20 particles  \n  - z: (0.4/0.02) = 20 particles\n  - Total: 20*20*20 = 8,000\n\n- Sand bed: (-0.8, -0.5, -0.8) to (0.8, -0.3, 0.8), spacing 0.04\n  - x: (1.6/0.04) = 40 particles\n  - y: (0.2/0.04) = 5 particles\n  - z: (1.6/0.04) = 40 particles\n  - Total: 40*5*40 = 8,000\n\nThat gives ~16K total which is reasonable (the spec says \"~10K each\" but 8K is close enough, and the total ~16K is within the 20K budget). The MAX_PARTICLES of 30K leaves room.\n\nNow let me also make sure the `sorted_hashes` passed to `build_data_struct` has the right slicing. The `sort_by_hash` writes into `w.sorted_hashes` which is the full max_particles array. The `sorted_hashes[:n]` slice should work correctly.\n\nLet me now update progress.md and commit."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":374,"cache_read_input_tokens":113538,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":374},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20e7fc32-9409-45e1-9ca1-0f98b4ecc786","uuid":"e8e54b8e-c503-4268-8b66-9cb84b501645"}
